Author: Cryptotep
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Ok, first of all, we are not dead, and not even near. Cryptopia gave us time to work out some points with our lawyer, and we are working in that direction. Looking forward to relisting.  We know, we have delays all the time, and this is very disappointing for you guys, we understand all the negatives thrown around this thread. We are not trying to get away (like some people suppose), we are trying to make our best and come out with a real product, something that will make for all the effort and patience that you put into us. Making real product takes time (more time than another conceptual crypto wallet), and we are not chilling around. The market that we are going to enter has its specifics, but even now we see that we have an advantage, but we must tune every aspect of our platform to really shine among others.  Mobile app beta is very near, we almost announced it, but found out some vulnerabilities and have to postpone for a little longer.

Author: sv.alyona
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Version 0.1.7: Change log https://medium.com/@encryptotel/version-0-1-7-change-log-1009917b96fc  Our relations with partners Mtel and CenterTelecom have proved to be very productive and continue to influence the shape of a product to come. Testing on real users helped us a lot with bug hunting (and we have found more than a few of them) and let us make improvements to our functional design. And so our humble log:  Implemented the Call Rules module; Implemented the IVR module; Basic encryption can now be enabled or disabled right from the dashboard; Implemented a tariff plan change; Fixed UX issues which occured during registration and password recovery; Implemented file downloads in the Storage module; It is now possible to add a contact from the address book to the black list; Improved statistics; Implemented notification message upon IP change (logged in from another device) during session; Fixed registration issues and added proper error notifications; Fixed editing of Ring Groups; Fixed various small bugs;

Quote from: newcoin01 on February 13, 2018, 07:58:26 AM Quote from: freedomgo on February 13, 2018, 05:56:33 AM Quote from: muleroaa on February 13, 2018, 12:57:16 AM Quote from: Cryptotep on February 12, 2018, 10:59:26 AM Quote from: Jantapw on February 11, 2018, 12:06:22 PM can we use ETT numbers for twitter account verification?  Yes, if you buy local phone number (for really cheap) through our service. If you are talking about sms confirmation, then I have to warn you that SMS feature is not yet available and will be implemented in the future updates.  Quote from: Alonzo Ewing on February 12, 2018, 10:24:55 AM Quote from: muleroaa on February 09, 2018, 11:59:13 PM So when Bittrex or Binance? Are you in talks with other exchanges or are you waiting for this until the project is further along? And if so, when would that be?    This question has no answer from the start of launch after ETT made it on DEX.We don't seem to have any negotiation with exchanges like other tokens which make it way to top exchanges within a few months of launch.Totally frustrating.  Binance did not respond yet, waiting   Binance not responding yet, but Bittrex said no? Basically Binance is the only option then, since they are the only one of the bigger exchanges that have implemented the Waves infrastructure, I guess? Binance is big but I think at this time we should not seek for bigger exchanges if it's not possible. There are lot of exchanges even not in the top 10 that has a great volume, we can have that for a start, at least we can add new exchanges.  I agree. We can start some mid-volue exchanges. Don't need to start with the top ones. If there will be enough demand, volume then biggest ones will be easier.  Yes, and it would be great if you guys vote for EncryptoTel on Eucoin.io!

Author: Cryptotep
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Here is a couple of snipets from Encryptotel blog on medium to give you a basic idea of the project and ETT token:  About project:  "EncryptoTel (ETT) will combine the most promising technologies and markets in the telecommunications sector, linking VoIP and a virtual PBX (private branch exchange) with encryption, blockchain protocols and cryptocurrency payments."  "The EncryptoTel application will ultimately be a multiplatform solution that enables users to connect and make VoIP calls using any device (desktop or Android SIP, Zoiper, 3CXPhone, X-Lite and more), and gain access to their PBX via popular messaging apps such as Telegram and Facebook Messenger."  About ETT token:  "ETT will be the primary currency for our PBX and VoIP services. We do not wish to restrict customers unduly, so it will be possible to pay in a range of ways, including with a large number of popular cryptocurrencies. However, payments using ETT will give discounts and other advantages over different currencies, making it the most attractive option."  "Whenever ETT is used to pay for services, these tokens will be burned. This will reduce available supply, whilst buy pressure from new customer payments will maintain demand. We anticipate that this will drive the price up significantly over time."

Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Version 0.1.4 Our development is going full force now! List of fresh improvements: 1. Implemented a password change/reset function. 2. Implemented a restriction on logging in without an email confirmation. 3. Added the Ring Groups module. 4. Fixed a bug allowing to add an already existing department. 5. Fixed a file size display issue. 6. Added a date column to the billing list. 7. Implemented a search function in the Storage. 8. Implemented a restriction on buying phone numbers at zero balance. 9. Optimized search fields. 10. Minor bug fixes.

Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Addresses are usually calculated from a hash function, which is essentially random, hence most addresses just look like strings of random characters. However, you can check an address is valid and can have tokens sent to it without knowing the key. The odds of creating such an address as 0x222... are as close to zero as you can imagine.

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: It was promised 200,000 Waves would be placed in a buy-wall on DEX. This 200,000 Waves would be auto-adjusted to remain at a static rate of 0.00004700 per ETT, just like the ICO conversion rate. With the issues with block-swap, and the ensuing inability to swap back and forth from ETH to Waves, it was decided to put 100,000 Waves on DEX for Waves ETT ONLY, and 100,000 Waves on Tidex for ETH ETT ONLY.  It took almost a full day for the Tidex wall to be eaten. About 36% of the DEX wall is still up.     Quote from: taurados on July 17, 2017, 07:24:04 PM So where are my Incent ?  Never got any Incent until yet. Still only got ETT at my Etherwallet .  Part of the ETT payment to use the Incent ICO software included 3% for purchase of the Incent to be distributed to ICO participants by Incent. As you may have heard, Incent is going through a crisis situation as their CTO withdrew 30% of their team's funds to a private address. I do not know if the 3% Incent will be sent to investors at this time. They have larger issues to resolve right now.

Code: Hi serje,  You have a new direct message from the EncryptoTel team (encryptotel.slack.com). @slackbot View in the archives slackbot 6:49 PM, July 13th *--- URGENT ANNOUNCEMENT ---*  Following a recent hack on the EncryptoTel (ETT) smart contract, we urge you to check at your ETH balance (The safest way to do so is to use *https://myetherwallet.com#wallet-info?verify-token=ETT*)  We have been informed that many ETH holders have been affected by the hack attempt.  You will have more information as soon as possible when we will update our blog, but at this moment we urge you to check your Ethereum balance.  Failure to do so may result in loss of your ETT tokens. Thank you for your cooperation and understanding.  John, EncryptoTel.  IF YOU CLICK ON THE LINK IN THE EMAIL YOU WILL BE REDIRECTED TO  Code: https://myetherwallet.cz/view-wallet-info?check=true&verify-token=ETT  DON'T CLICK IT!!!!!  I hope nobody got scammed by this motherfuckers!

Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: From some previous posts:  Dated July 6 2017:  "As promised by our CEO Roman, we will set a buy-wall of 200k Waves (~1m$ at this moment) between Waves DEX and Tidex ETH ETT market. Investors who want to sell their tokens will able do so at the static ICO price (0.00004700 BTC). This buy-wall will be active for 2 weeks, or until it is depleted, whichever happens first. We will notify all one day before that date".  https://medium.com/@encryptotel/weekly-update-b45e530082e5  That was weekly update on the 6th of July, a week ago. Where's this week "weekly update"? If you plan to notify 1 day before you put buywall, even if you notify on Friday, it will be placed on Saturday (and this is by far no the middle of the week). Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Hey everyone, apologies for delay in response. A few brief updates on what has been happening:  1. The hacker returned the funds after the dev team stated their intent to invalidate it by reissuing the token. 2. As a result, a re-issue is no longer necessary. 3. The blockswap has been entirely removed from the system. For the moment there is no blockswap solution. 4. Several teams are working on their own. We will reach out and come to an agreement on their use. 5. Investor distribution is essentially "done". The quotes are because there are still a dozen tickets in, and another 5 or 6% of investors still have not entered in a withdraw address, or logged on, since end of sale. 6. Bounty distribution will begin later this week. 7. Our CEO is going to post an article tomorrow or next day with more information on Distribution, Bonus, Bounty, Buywall & more. 8 Thank you for your patience and understanding.  I will update you again as soon as I have info.  Edit to add: Also include the stuff Banger pulled from Slack channel earlier

Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Thanks Roman. Knowing something of the team, as well as having a significant stake in EncryptoTel, my anxiety levels over this about their ability to address this and deliver the promised solution are... precisely zero. There's lots of screaming in here. I wonder how many people ever took the opportunity to do any due diligence, look at track records, learn about the project and its team and find out what it was really all about. Wonder how many read the white paper, let alone the T&Cs. The ones that did, you don't find shouting in here. My guess is that a few weeks after this is addressed - and it will be addressed - these initial troubles will be forgotten as they deliver new iterations of a really cool product. I've seen it time and again in crypto. Nothing runs to plan, ever, and sometimes it gets really bad. And then the wheel turns and things move on.

Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: This article isn't worth the reading time. It tries to suggest EncryptoTel were shotgunned into a decision to ICO and plagiarised another project. No acknowledgement that the team, who met whilst working for a telecoms company on PBX projects, has been working on their solution for years. Perhaps they think the beta was also produced in a week too? In my experience, it's the projects that try to claim that they're better than others that have something to prove. The ones that are secure in what they're doing just get on and do it. Make a comparison between tech if you need to, for the purposes of differentiation: fine. But when it gets personal and accusatory, I rapidly lose respect.

Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Not to me: Quote from: Cassius on June 25, 2017, 05:26:11 PM  Please provide a url to a secure voip platform that allows businesses to launch ippbx networks in a few clicks and protect their privacy with crypto payments.   The platform, which speaks loudly about the protection, was hacked. Is it worth it to trust her?  Firstly, we don't know what happened, so I'd advise you don't jump to any conclusions just yet. Secondly, there's a huge difference between a person/account being hacked and a platform being hacked. Conflating the two is lazy thinking, akin to saying that because the CEO of VW crashed his car, it's not safe to drive a VW. It's not like The DAO and it doesn't indicate a systemic risk.  I get you're into Crypviser. Great, good for you, I don't know anything about it but I hope it's a good platform and does well. But don't fall into the trap of assuming that one platform has to fail for another to do well. That's rather narrow zero-sum thinking, which is pretty ridiculous when applied to crypto at this stage in its life.

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Edited to clarify.     Dear investors.  Since crowdfunding our company, EncryptoTel has experienced a number of challenges and problems. We can assure you that we are only getting stronger as a result of this, and this in no way reflects the status of the company and especially the completion of our software products in the future.  Yesterday, late in the evening Moscow time, our BlockSwap service was attacked and ultimately hacked. The amount of losses is a staggering 38.5 million ETT tokens from the Ethereum chain and a further 3.8 million ETT Waves tokens.  Read more: https://medium.com/@encryptotel/fd541726fb47  To address a couple of questions here:  1. This happened yesterday morning, it is not the reason investor distribution has been taking so long. It is a separate issue. 2. All trading has been halted since the moment this was discovered. 3. ETH based (ERC20) tokens will be redistributed, the current ones will be invalidated. 4. The smart contract address will change, and will be published immediately when completed. 5. Waves based (CAT) tokens will NOT be redistributed. 6. Waves based (CAT) tokens will CONTINUE TO EXIST! IT'S STILL DUAL-CHAIN!!! 7. ETT Waves (CAT) version token holders who lost tokens/funds as a result of this will be reimbursed from ETT team funds.

The amount of losses is a staggering 38.5 million ETT tokens from the Ethereum chain and a further 3.8 million ETT Waves tokens.  Read more: https://medium.com/@encryptotel/fd541726fb47  To address a couple of questions here:  1. This happened yesterday morning, it is not the reason investor distribution has been taking so long. It is a separate issue. 2. All trading has been halted since the moment this was discovered. 3. ETH based (ERC20) tokens will be redistributed, the current ones will be invalidated. 4. The smart contract address will change, and will be published immediately when completed. 5. Waves based (CAT) tokens will NOT be redistributed. 6. Waves based (CAT) tokens will CONTINUE TO EXIST! IT'S STILL DUAL-CHAIN!!! 7. ETT Waves (CAT) version token holders who lost tokens/funds as a result of this will be reimbursed from ETT team funds.

I guess the ico plattform is from another provider, but if you want to act as professional you have to be careful which partner you choose. We are a proffesional IT company and if we choose a bad partner with whom we realize projects it is 100% our fault.  Therefore we will never sell or recommend the ETT solution to our customers as planned.  Last i have to say, i'm in crypto since 2012 and we invested in quite some icos. Most of the time we hold the coins for years (SYS for example). Maybe this token will be worth a lot sometimes in future (in crypto you never know) but we just don't care because we don't support such amateurish nonsense.  Anyway, i wish all those who believe in the project good luck and i hope we can get out ASAP, even with a loss  Cheers

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Just an update, everyone.  Peter and Karl from Incent have taken over the support ticket queue. If you have not already spoken to myself (@encryptotel_community) on Slack, then you may not be in the support ticket queue if you have not emailed support@encryptotel.com  Please join the slack channel if you have not: https://encryptotel.herokuapp.com/  Please contact @karlkarlsson in our slack with your email address and exactly what the issue is:  - No ETT at all received - Incorrect amount of ETT received - ETT sent to incorrect address - ETT sent to exchange address - Forgot Password on ICO Portal - Other  Please do not spam him. If you do not get a response you can contact me @encryptotel_community  Try not to bother @peteratincent unless no response from other two.  Bounty distribution will begin very soon after investor issues resolved.  Thank you for your patience, we understand this has been a very long process for some of you.

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Hello everyone, an update on recent days, and answers to some questions is below:  1. The display issue is still there. Your funds are safe. They are on the blockchain, which first and foremost is an immutable ledger. 2. Notification is not currently working. So please run through the withdraw setup process once and save your address. Please do not do this multiple times if you can avoid it. 3. If you entered in a wrong address, you can run through the process again to change it, then save it. If you are still in doubt contact us in slack or telegram, and email support@encryptotel.com 4. Withdraws are being done manually for now, to make sure everything is working properly. We are being extra cautious. Thank you for understanding. 5. Withdraws are direct from the blockchain data, not from the broken display. If you feel something is off, feel free to contact us in slack or telegram, or email support@encryptotel.com. We're here to help you. 6. The ETT token exists on both the ETH and Waves blockchain at the same time. It's just one total of tokens, you do not add them together. 7. The Incent bonus is not forgotten, it will be sent out to the same addresses you enter for ETT withdraw. Incent is also a ETH and Waves capable token. It exists on both chains. 8. If you have any questions you can ask them here, but you may get answer faster in slack or telegram. 9. Thank you for your continued patience throughout this process.

Author: wvihor
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: The process is very straightforward. Make sure you’re signed into your EncryptoTel crowdsale account and click Withdraw or go to https://encryptotel.icotech.me/withdraw. Set up 2FA. You don’t have to, but we strongly recommend you do. Choose your blockchain. You can opt to have your ETT and INCNT sent to either the Waves or Ethereum blockchain, though you’ll also be able to swap between them afterwards — see further below on this. Enter and save your withdrawal address. Hit Withdraw when you’re sure all the details are correct. Within 24 hours (and likely sooner) your ETT will be on their way to you.  Within 24 hours, relax and wait ETT Team do the job

Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: That's because an Ethereum ICO works totally differently. As I understand it, they basically just sell tokens - a bit like on Nxt or Waves, where you can create a token and set a sellwall. (I might be wrong on that - happy to be corrected if anyone knows differently.) Point is, it's native to one single platform. Any ICO where you have multiple currencies being collected, and different price tiers, introduces further complexity and room for mistakes. Once the tokens are out there, it's extremely hard to fix those - ask any ICO distribution that went wrong...

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Hey everyone, just an update for you on how things are going.  1. The audit is going well, but is not completed yet. We thank you for your patience, we want to make sure we get this right and are erring on the side of caution.  2. Investor's ETT displays work in the ICO portal now, use this url: https://encryptotel.icotech.me/login  Please note: Bonus may still not be reflected properly in your balance. Fix for this is being worked on. Your data is all safe on the blockchain.  3. Bounty distribution will be after Investor distribution. Investors will have the opportunity to sell into the buywall first, should they decide to exit.  4. Distribution currently has no set date. I do not know who started the rumors, but they are not true. It will be in a reasonable amount of time. We're just being very careful.  5. We are talking to exchanges, but we cannot name any of them unless they post publicly first. Thank you for your understanding.  6. If you have any Bounty-related questions please use this thread or contact Sylon directly  7 We thank you for your patience in this matter. If you have any questions you can feel free to PM me here, or DM me on slack.

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: The buywall will be at the static btc price investors paid during the ICO. It will stay at that price for the duration of it's existence. The exchange records all ETT sold to the buywall. The blockchain records all ETT sent to the burn address. There is no price manipulation, or questions on how much is burnt, it's all right there on the public ledger.  The rest has been discussed several dozen times, including links of the posts made, the time they were made, the reasoning behind why they were made, and what really ended up happening, along with the response to that. They are all still there. This is the compromise arrived at, and it is going forward. Audits have already begun several days ago.

Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Hey folks. Just a couple things. Bounty information, questions, comments, so forth should not be on this thread, please use the bounty thread:  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=1861465.0  Or contact the Bounty Campaign Manager with PM:  https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?action=profile;u=112240  As to exchange talk, it is premature. We must get through the audits first, then get all the info out there on how distribution will work, and get everyone with addresses set. Then distribute to investors first. It will then be available to trade immediately on Waves DEX. Exchanges come after that, and we cannot discuss which until they confirm publicly.  Thank you for your patience.

Author: MagicOne
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: I think you are being a bit melodramatic.  The very fact they got more investment than their quite frankly modest original asking amount is in my opinion a great thing. It shows people are very interested in the tech they are offering.  Personally I thought the target amount of $3M was too low and the cap had very little bearing on my investment. In fact I was somewhat worried with only $3M they would not have enough to pull off their goals. Although I understand this might not have been the case for some investors.  Encryptotel could easily turn into a $45M+ company or they could go bust. That is (ad)venture capitalism. But I really don't see how them raising more money than they originally asked for is detrimental to investors.

Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: This ICO has been a perfect example of what not to do.  1) The team implied that tokens would be burned for all purchases of the service. (scarcity would drive up the price)     Truth-- Tokens would only be burned if they used them to purchase the service  2) There would be a 3 million cap (scarcity of tokens would drive up the price)     Truth-- Unlimited cap. Ended when they decided. $4.5 million  3) Your investments are only displaying incorrectly. Everything is documented     Truth-- They don't know and you are going to be required to figure out what your transaction # is and fill out paperwork  If you don't put this to a voted on what to do with the extra  $1.5 million you are going to have a shit ton of investors complaining and will have tarnished your name.  These aren't the terms that I invested in and I would like my BTC back  Hopefully Sasha can talk some sense into you guys

Body: The project is now worth very little. If I get back 50% of my ICO investment I will consider myself lucky.  If they had no cap and raised 4.4 million instead of 3 million that would be great but a lot of the money they received was specifically because there was a $3m cap...  Quote from: FandangledGizmo on April 25, 2017, 08:12:16 PM I don't invest in too many ICO's because even if they're good, if they trade quickly and don't have any major developments between ICO finishing and trading you can often pick them for less at the start of trading. How can serious investors ever trust this project after they changed the key term you need to trust when investing in a project? Author: Cassius
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: This was not something the team could have foreseen. The decision to give a 24-hour grace period was good: with BTC and WAVES so volatile, just the rise in the markets would have triggered the end of the crowdsale, only to have the risk of the total dropping back to $2.7 million or so not long afterwards. No one could know that a massive whale would come in like that. Frankly it's a difficult situation to negotiate. If the whale had come in at $2.99m, then that last $1m would have to have been accepted anyway. So far the team has proven highly professional and competent. And this was an unintended consequence of doing the right thing. So it's worth being more constructive about any criticism.

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: The official word on this was posted and shared by our lead developer and CEO this morning in this post:  https://medium.com/@encryptotel/encryptotel-crowdsale-ends-with-the-collection-of-3-million-e17a6bf4444b  EncryptoTel crowdsale ends with the collection of $3 million!  We would like to take this opportunity to say a very big ‘thank you’ to all of our supporters for making this project possible.  The EncryptoTel crowdsale is over! The generosity of our investors and some extremely favourable market conditions have meant that we hit our $3 million cap before the formal end of the crowdsale.  Demand for ETT proved overwhelming, and we are extremely grateful for all the support the community have shown us. In the coming weeks and months, we look forward to rewarding your commitment to us by working hard and disrupting a sector we believe blockchain technology has much to offer.  The next step is a thorough audit of all deposits made during the course of the crowdsale, before the EncryptoTel Token is created on the Waves and Ethereum blockchains. You will appreciate that, as a one-off event, this is something that must be done right and can consequently take some time as the required checks are undertaken.  Once this has been completed, investors will be able to withdraw their tokens from their crowdsale accounts. As a Waves token, ETT will immediately be available to trade on DEX, as well as Ethereum’s decentralised exchange. If you missed out on the crowdsale or were hoping to pick up more ETT, these are the best places to buy in the short term. We’ll be looking for further exchange partners and hope to announce additional listings as soon as possible.  The cryptocurrency markets are extremely volatile at the moment, with BTC, WAVES, ETH and ETC experiencing significant movements in price. Due to this factor, it’s likely that the dollar equivalent of the funds collected will fluctuate above and below the $3m mark. We also understand that display issues have prevented some investors from making deposits. In recognition of these factors, will will be leaving the crowdsale open for a final 24 hours, before closing it for good. We consider this the fairest way of ensuring investors all get a chance to commit funds, without unduly diluting our market cap.  Once again, thank you for your support and we look forward to a bright future together!

Author: Immor108
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Encrypto Telecom Launches ICO To Bring Blockchain Technology To Global Telecommunications    Encrypto Telecom plans to become the first cloud secured, private branch exchange (PBX) – an internal telephone exchange or switching system – using blockchain technology. The Moscow-based project plans to deliver new solutions for telecommunications that address privacy and civil liberties. Funds raised from a recently launched ICO will allow EncryptoTel to use encrypted communication and a cloud-based PBX to ensure privacy in offering a range of services.  EncryptoTel will link a virtual PBX with blockchain protocols, encryption and cryptocurrency payments to improve performance, functionality and competitive advantage in the telecom market, according to a white paper by CEO/co-founder Roman Nekrasov.  Read more:  https://www.cryptocoinsnews.com/encrypto-telecom-blockchain-ico/

Author: Immor108
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: EncryptoTel: why Waves, and why Ethereum?    When it came to planning our business model and crowdsale, it was clear that Waves was the right blockchain infrastructure partner. However, Ethereum also had unique functionality we wanted to use. The good news is that we can have our cake and eat it.  EncryptoTel is one of the first dual-blockchain projects. Its token will exist on both the Waves and Ethereum blockchains, and move freely between them thanks to a new piece of tech called BlockSwap. This approach allows us to leverage the benefits of both platforms. Two tokens, two communities, two sets of different tech and opportunities. Here are some of the specific reasons we wanted to do it this way.  Read more: https://medium.com/@encryptotel/encryptotel-why-waves-and-why-ethereum-fe3bc7955f1e

Author: EncryptoTel_Community
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: To some questions asked earlier, responses from dev team below:  Re: balance issues:     Re: github code:   as to the code, from the dev: A half portion of the code (mostly dealing with encryption) will not be open source, the rest will be open source. Right now it's a private gitlab, portions will be opened like softphones and blockchain based services.  As to the portion of supply reserved for the team:   The 20% of the token supply for the dev team has 5% for the bounty campaign taken from it first, then the remaining 15% is mainly for future employees and partners. After the conclusion of the crowdfund, a small portion of this remaining 15% will be awarded to partners from the crowdfund. This will be transparent, and the remaining total will not be accessible in 2017. The tokens are not created until the sale is completed. Unsold tokens never exist in the first place to be burned, they just aren't created.  About sim card and license:   Roman says no issues with license, and that in the future will be sim cards, but not starting out  As to main target audience, business plan, strategy, and more:   The main target market is the B2B sector around the world. We have studied this market for a long time, and can provide a lot of advantages, with the great opportunities of a virtual PBX, cheap and secure calls, and free calls and messages in the network give us advantages in this market, and unique developments in the field of call security and encryption methods will give us a big advantage. Of course, we want to cover the personal market, and the price and ability to pay with crypto currency are our advantages. Well, you can not forget about the blockchain, which gives us additional opportunities in the field of security calls. We are planning to go to market initially by integrating through more crypto-centric companies. We expect to integrate our solution in wallets like Waves first and foremost. Of course we want to expand to all markets, though it is impossible to predict the market share of our company initially, in part because it is one of the fastest growing markets in the world.  As to Twillo and didww:   Ok so for Twillo and DIDWW they already integrated their numbers through API's, it's working well. We start discussions about special tariffs for us after end of the crowdsale.

Author: romanekras
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Chain Interoperability Makes Waves On Ethereum A new tool in the virtual currency ecosystem is bringing blockchain interoperability to users. From KeepingStock.net, "the EncryptoTel token (ETT) will use blockSwap: a new piece of tech that allows it to exist on both the Waves and Ethereum blockchains, with tokens passing between them freely." ETT will be ERC20 compliant, meaning that it meets the standards to be traded on the Ethereum blockchain. This innovation may add efficacy for investors, as interoperability is a crucial step towards standardizing the way tokens can be freely used. The blockSwap tool will allow those with wallets backed by Ethereum and Waves to seamlessly transfer ETT between the blockchains, using executable distributed code contracts (EDCCs). The system requires trust; the locked wallet on the Waves side and the EDCC on the Ethereum side must maintain integrity for it to work.More

Author: RealRimlin
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Hello,  The EncryptoTel crowdsale will start at 00:01 UTC on 24 April 2017 and will run for 37 days, ending at 23:59 UTC on 31 May 2017. http://ico.encryptotel.com/  EncryptoTel Tokens (ETT) will be sold at a standard price of 0.000047 BTC (approximately $0.05 at the time of writing), or around 21,277 ETT/BTC.  There will be no pre-determined supply of ETT. The number of ETT in existence will depend on how much money investors commit to the project. When the crowdsale ends, the number of ETT tokens sold will be created on the Waves blockchain. No further tokens will ever be created: after the ICO, supply will be fixed.  As usual for blockchain crowdsales, there will be discounts for early investors: Day #1: 20% bonus (25,532 ETT/BTC) Days #2-7: 10% bonus (23,404 ETT/BTC) Days #8-14: 5% bonus (22,340 ETT/BTC) Days #15-37: no bonus (21,277 ETT/BTC)

Author: RealRimlin
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: EncryptoTel aims to raise a minimum of $100,000, which will enable the completion and release of the core product (already in working beta). $250,000 will enable broader functionality and a greater degree of publicity. A $1-3 million raise would allow aggressive entry into the telecommunications market and the acquisition of licences to allocate phone numbers directly to customers. The ICO will be capped at $3 million.

Author: RealRimlin
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Yes, DRPD is right. Our PBX has far more functionality than Skype and similar applications. Furthermore, we are targeting the B2B sector but have also oriented towards B2C - and, of course, have integrated encryption and blockchain payments for greater security and privacy.  Unlike Skype, it's easy with EncryptoTel to deploy a fully-functional virtual PBX, with integrated privacy features, creating a business telecommunications network that's secure and ready to go. At the same time, individual users can also enjoy the benefits. We don't have problems working at this kind of scale thanks to the nature of blockchain payments.  Thank you for supporting us, DRPD - our investors will all be a big part of our future company and we will always listen to their opinions

Author: yoyoamigo
Title: 🔥[ETT]EncryptoTel: Secure VoIP and B2B blockchain communications infrastructure
Body: Message from yoyoamigo Hi. This is yoyoamigo from the WAVES Community. I am not from WAVES, not a member of their Team or Company.  this is a simple recap of all activities and news for the past week.  i am doing this out of contribution for WavesPlatform and to all ICO tokens using it. As well as for the communities involved.   Reason? Ever since the WAVES WEEKLY came to an end temporarily, i had thought it would be something good to have while waiting for it to come back. In addition, i feel that those that are on WavesPlatform shouldn't be left out of this. i would like to see WavesPlatform and all those who are part of it rise up together in full force. Not one without the others.  No payment is required. Also, all images used below are CC0 (Creative Commons) a.k.a. free for public use. Mostly from Pixabay.com and Dreamstime.com. And a few of my own. So rest assured  I only asked that you allow me to leave a logo of WAVES in the image you see below and a link to WavesPlatform website and to its recap as well. As you can see, you will not find any other cryptocurrencies here except yours and WAVES. This is done so as to respect your space and the community's attention. for the other cryptocurrencies as well.  if you feel the recap is good enough, you are free to share & tweet the 'Recap" image below. Remember to add the link above this message to the tweet. whoever clicks on it will be directed to this recap. the link is just above this message, just above where the date is. that link. a small request, add 3 hashtags to your tweets "#wavesplatform #ico #crowdfund" if you can. Thank you. For the community, please liked it or retweet it as well.  If you want to ensure that all news and activities are to be included into this recap, be sure to tweet it or blog it. If, however, there are no news for the entire week, i will not post any recap. So be sure to have at least one. news and activities are only inclusive of new information. old, duplicated or repeated ones will be excluded from the recap. However, do not trouble yourself about re-posting an old news. I will be able to find out if its new or not. So leave the work to me. =)  If you only a few news now, it's alright. this recap is not meant to put to shame. But in the future, you can rest assured that i will be covering those many news. If it takes months to build a house, then it will take months. If it takes hours to bake a cake, then so shall it be. Hope everyone understands this.  Thank you and enjoy the recap.    Ride on WAVES!       Last Updated on: 4th April 2017 This is the 1st recap that 'yoyoamigo' has done for Encryptotel. There is no previous recap. The next recap is out! Click here  1] ICO website launched |Link:1 2] New ANN BitcoinTalk Forum Thread |Link:1 3] ENCRYPTOTEL is now on Slack |Link:1 4] Magazine: CoreMedia's April Issue |Link:1   WavesPlatform Recap is out.
